reviews.review_text: Circle Jerk "actually saw the band in '83-'86". What the hell is that supposed to mean? Sounds like you 86'd in '86. Seeing shows from '83-'86 certainly does make one a Dead Head. LOL! If you can "please explain" what a "goodchin a cat" or a "ud Dead Head" is, I still won't explain to you what "sick" means. You would think the 5 star rating I gave it would have provided you with a clue, although I can see how your view would be obstructed, I mean with your head up some guy's ass and all. Crawl out from under your rock - or, um, 69 teabag, wash the man goo off your hands so your fingers don't stick to the keys as you type, and get some fresh air! It's 2009! And it's sickness!

Please explain.. does "sick sick sick" mean it is a goodchin a cat or a bad one?  ud Dead Heads who actually saw the band in '83-'86 never used the word sick to describe a show.  Thanks.

I love the Greek, saw the '85 and '86 shows there, this is a solid run not spectacular, well played all nights.
SICK! I'm a deadhead who saw shows in the '83-'86 period and I'd say this show is EXTREMELY sick, not just well played. I said it then and still do...

Too funny! Hey Undejohn, NO SHIT! I mean what kind of name is "teabag69" anyway! Not that you will ever come back to see this post, but to anyone else who reads this, let me tell you, if you are not reading the "reviews" at the bottom of the page on these shows, you are missing the real entertainment here! I am now scrolling ever so slowly through all the years just reading the hilarious banter back and forth between 70's and 80's Heads. So much for peace and love. ho ho bro! Would make a great Saturday Night Live skit or something. 

Oh, and by the way, I give this show a solid 4 stars for quality of sound and IMHO the band was smokin!

I love it.

Another Great Show From the Greek  Great sound quality for an AUD recording. Phil is all over this show and it shows up well in the mix. The band is firing on all cylinders this night as they usually are at the Greek. Jerry's ripping it up on a great Know You Rider, a nice jazzy Eyes and an unusually long Throwing Stones. Can't see why this show hasn't ever gotten more attention. Not a spectacular set list but some great,breezy playing. Feels just like an early summer day......well worth the DL
